            <title>[JDK-8316661] CompilerThread leaks CodeBlob memory when dynamically stopping compiler thread in non-product</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8316661</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>CodeBlob::flush() is not called when a compiler thread is stopped due to dynamic compiler thread policy (and during shutdown of the compiler runtime).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This leaks memory (asm_strings and dbg_strings allocated memory) in non-product builds.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
